Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Scaphoid pseudarthrosis' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Normal' radio button is enabled
And 'Diffuse edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial necrosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Complete necrosis' radio button is enabled

And 'Stage I: resorption zone parallel to fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage II: cyst formation' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage III: sclerosis' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage IV: secondary osteoarthritis' radio button is enabled

And 'Stage I' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage II' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage III' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Stage II: cyst formation' radio button
Then 'A: Stable' radio button is enabled
And 'B: Unstable' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Stage III: sclerosis' radio button
Then 'With osteophytes: hypertrophic' radio button is enabled
And 'Without osteophytes: atrophic' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Stage IV: secondary osteoarthritis' radio button
Then 'A: Between radius and distal fragment' radio button is enabled
And 'B: Between proximal fragment and os capit
And 'C: Between os lunatum and os capitatum' radio button is enabled
